and we've also spoken to the palestinian leadership because there's every evidence that these riots are not just spontaneous and homegrown
but we have spoken, and we have _ and that's why _ part of the reason why the secretary of state is going back over there
we don't support that sort of thing, and we're trying to persuade all the participants to try to arrive at a solution representing justice for all
q. well, if you want that, and you say you believe in security for israel and legitimate rights of the palestinians, why don't you go on the public record now and say that there should be an exchange _ a removal of the occupation and a peace?
a. well, i don't think it's up to us to dictate a settlement in the middle east
q. we are great supporters of israel, so we certainly have some influence
