he said there also will be training seminars and other events at which democrats will be advised how to cross over and obtain gop ballots in order to support robertson in the may 3 primary
however ohio law will require a strategy adjustment because it requires voters to register 30 days before the primary. while registrants do not declare their party affiliations up front, they later join one of the major parties by requesting its ballot at the polling place
democrats or republicans already registered on may 3, as a result of past voting, can cross over by signing a statement that they now support the principles of the other party, jeske pointed out
