we do have have some people outside who are not believing us,'' said centrum marketing director kathleen heinz. ``they think they will be more tickets. we're telling them that's not the case. the tickets are all sold.''
more than 13,000 fans held tickets for the thursday night concert
during an appearance wednesday in boston, springsteen promised ``plenty of surprises'' in the three sold-out dates at the arena
worcester police deputy chief edward o'brien said 30 officers were stationed at the centrum for crowd control and to hunt down ticket scalpers, who reportedly were reaping up to $600 a ticket
a 23-year-old worcester man was arrested after he allegedly sold two $20 tickets to a plainclothes police officer for $400. police seized four tickets to thursday's show and two for the final worcester show on monday, and the man was fined $525 for reselling tickets and selling tickets without a license
and in case anyone was wondering, worcester cobbler david jennette says springsteen wears a size 10d boot
i didn't believe it when we got the call tuesday night asking if we'd do some work on bruce springsteen's boots. i thought it was a prank,'' jennette said. ``we were just closing up so i said `ok, come right over,' thinking it was some kid calling up.''
it was no joke. a few minutes later, springsteen's road manager appeared with a pair of boots and asked to have the leather soles replaced with non-skid rubber soles
jennette was invited to springsteen's rehearsal and took his sister-in-law along
bruce was great. after the rehearsal he came over and talked to us and let us take pictures with him,'' he said
