i see no fear for her (tawana), her family, her lawyers and myself for going to jail,'' said sharpton, who said he met earlier thursday with the brawley family. ``you're probably safer in jail than you are in the streets.''
miss brawley was found wrapped in a garbage bag and covered with feces, with racial insults scrawled on her body, after being missing for four days last november. she said she was assaulted by six white men, one of whom flashed a police badge
