motion sensors that control lights will be installed in the next few weeks in all restrooms of the building occupied by cities service oil and gas corp
the sensors will detect motion when people pass and turn on lights. if no motion is detected for 12 minutes, the devices will turn the lights out, according to the memo
a spokesman said the devices have been tested in one men's room in the building and have been found to be effective in reducing electricity use
