the stock market staged a strong advance today, reviving its recent rally after sluggish showings in the past two sessions
the dow jones average of 30 industrials jumped 27.69 to 2,067.64 by noontime on wall street, making a run at new highs since the crash last fall
advancing issues outnumbered declines by more than 5 to 2 in the overall tally of new york stock exchange-listed issues, with 1,022 up, 376 down and 433 unchanged
before the opening the commerce department said the nation's gross nation product grew at a 4.5 percent annual rate, after adjustment for inflation, in the fourth quarter of last year
the department had previously estimated the pace of growth for the october-december period at 4.2 percent
the upward revision was somewhat smaller than some analysts had been expecting. but traders still apparently saw it as a plus for the business outlook
many wall streeters were still watching to see whether the dow jones industrials can close above the 2,051.89 mark reached on jan. 7, which stands as the average's high since the crash last october
